{"TopicId":204148,"ForumId":109,"TopicTitle":"Question: Launching/Building Colonies","CreatedByName":"Space Kerbalisation Tech","CreatedById":211297,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-02T13:04:30Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Space Kerbalisation Tech","CreatedById":211297,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-02T13:04:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u2019m not sure if this is the right place to post this, but i have a pretty burning question about colonies in ksp2. From the trailer and many other posts about what ksp2 will be like, it seems like they are pretty hard to launch and/or build. I imagine the will have to be built on site using \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E (kinda like\u00A0to eva construction mode, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0or extraplanetry launchpads conbined?) because stuff like this seems unable to be launched and landed with anything less than 1000 parts, which in this case my potato pc will self combust.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes anyone know how exactly colonies can be built and assembled? (hopefully this will not be related to me not reading dev diaries/other ksp2 stuff close enough\u00A0)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-02T13:13:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224013466\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204148\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221627909470\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211297\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Space Kerbalisation Tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Space Kerbalisation Tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit seems like they are pretty hard to launch and/or build.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou build them on sight\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224013466\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204148\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221627909470\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211297\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Space Kerbalisation Tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Space Kerbalisation Tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhich in this case my potato pc will self combust.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP 2 will be much more optimised than KSP 1, which has been known for a very long time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224013466\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204148\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221627909470\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211297\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Space Kerbalisation Tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Space Kerbalisation Tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(hopefully this will not be related to me not reading dev diaries/other ksp2 stuff close enough\u00A0)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell it will be lol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pthigrivi","CreatedById":105624,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-02T13:55:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/211297-space-kerbalisation-tech/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022211297\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/211297-space-kerbalisation-tech/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Space Kerbalisation Tech\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0 We don\u0027t know a whole lot yet, but it sounds like colonization will begin by manually landing a few starter modules and as you grow you\u0027ll be able to phase in modules built on site from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 These can be organized through a\u00A0\u0022Building Assembly Editor\u0022 that allows you to stack and assemble colonies similar to the way we build rockets in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.pcgamer.com/kerbal-space-program-2-dev-reveals-how-baby-kerbals-are-made/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.pcgamer.com/kerbal-space-program-2-dev-reveals-how-baby-kerbals-are-made/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-08-03T12:08:27Z\u0022 title=\u002208/03/2021 12:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 3, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Pthigrivi\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ballisticfox0","CreatedById":206207,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-02T15:41:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224013466\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204148\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221627909470\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211297\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Space Kerbalisation Tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Space Kerbalisation Tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u2019m not sure if this is the right place to post this, but i have a pretty burning question about colonies in ksp2. From the trailer and many other posts about what ksp2 will be like, it seems like they are pretty hard to launch and/or build. I imagine the will have to be built on site using \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E (kinda like\u00A0to eva construction mode, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0or extraplanetry launchpads conbined?) because stuff like this seems unable to be launched and landed with anything less than 1000 parts, which in this case my potato pc will self combust.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes anyone know how exactly colonies can be built and assembled? (hopefully this will not be related to me not reading dev diaries/other ksp2 stuff close enough\u00A0)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom what we have heard you will start by launching and landing smaller base buildings\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\neventually you will get the BAE\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhich allows you to build bases on site\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Space Kerbalisation Tech","CreatedById":211297,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-03T06:34:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah this seems to be everything that can be currently found now on colonies, thanks you all for your help\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;p\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/971609041_P.png\u0022 title=\u0022;p\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nlooking forward to the ksp2 release!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"intelliCom","CreatedById":209738,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-06T13:02:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224013471\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204148\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221627909994\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/2/2021 at 11:13 PM, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou build them on sight\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, you can\u0027t exactly build them without\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eseeing\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0them\u00A0now, can ya?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-08-06T13:47:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224015435\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204148\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u